  <div class='bigger'>What's up with hamsters?</div>
  <i>Hamsteren</i> in Dutch means <i>to hoard.</i> It's similar to the English phrase <i>to squirrel away</i>. A Japanese friend of mine told me that <i> to marmot</i> has a similar meaning in Japanese. If you know more examples of languages that use small critters to suggest hoarding please send me a mail and tell me about them.

